.TH "nilfs_ioctl_get_info" 9 "nilfs_ioctl_get_info" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nilfs_ioctl_get_info \- wrapping function of get metadata info
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nilfs_ioctl_get_info
.BI "(struct inode *inode "  ","
.BI "struct file *filp "  ","
.BI "unsigned int cmd "  ","
.BI "void __user *argp "  ","
.BI "size_t membsz "  ","
.BI "ssize_t (*dofunc)(struct the_nilfs *, __u64 *, int, void *, size_t, size_t) "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "inode" 12
inode object
.IP "filp" 12
file object
.IP "cmd" 12
ioctl's request code
.IP "argp" 12
pointer on argument from userspace
.IP "membsz" 12
size of an item in bytes
.IP "dofunc" 12
concrete function of getting metadata info
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBnilfs_ioctl_get_info\fP gets metadata info by means of
calling \fBdofunc\fP function.

Return Value: On success, 0 is returned and requested metadata info
is copied into userspace. On error, one of the following
negative error codes is returned.

-EINVAL - Invalid arguments from userspace.

-ENOMEM - Insufficient amount of memory available.

-EFAULT - Failure during execution of requested operation.
